issue.title: Consider adding file extensions to auto-mode-alist
issue.body:
Something like:
```elisp
(add-to-list 'auto-mode-alist '("\\.mmd$" . mermaid-mode)))
```

See also https://github.com/mermaid-js/mermaid/issues/147.

I picked `mmd` because github seems to support that.

comment.body: This change broke emacs: `Invalid regexp: "Trailing backslash"`
Move `|| echo "KGlobalSettings.notifyChange failed"` after done? So that if it fails we don't get 10 messages.

pull_request.title: kconifg:init
pull_request.body:
### Description
Fixes https://github.com/nix-community/home-manager/issues/607 by providing a way to programattically set kde configuration files. 
However as note that any theme changed with this module requires a logout, as the proper way would be to exec `plasma-apply-*` and those commands seem to require a working DBus and thus https://github.com/nix-community/home-manager/pull/2548 for testing on my setup.

comment.body: It's not implemented yet. In theory you can send small files using very low level net_crypto api, but proper implementation will require congestion control.

Derivation adds a bit more safety - if we need to add a new value to `LogType` without derivation we have to remember to add it to `value_variants` manually. Also there could be typos in manually written strings.
Yeah, but it's the purpose of this feature, and it can add dependencies only for `tox-node`. You thing we should avoid this? :)
Maybe derive this implementation: https://docs.rs/clap/latest/clap/trait.ValueEnum.html

issue.title: Fontify javap buffers in lsp-metals--decode
issue.body:
Hi, this PR activates `java-mode` in javap buffers generated by `lsp-metals--decode`:

![javap-fontified](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/17688577/190594972-f21fd7eb-d19c-40f9-8f09-ac778b21a014.png)

 and makes `lsp-metals-decode-file` a command which when not passed a format-id, will prompt the user for one from a preset list. I've also `defconst`ed all of the format ids so that they're not duplicated.

I hope this is helpful, thanks :slightly_smiling_face:

comment.body: Thanks.

issue.title: Fontify javap buffers in lsp-metals--decode
issue.body:
Hi, this PR activates `java-mode` in javap buffers generated by `lsp-metals--decode`:

![javap-fontified](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/17688577/190594972-f21fd7eb-d19c-40f9-8f09-ac778b21a014.png)

 and makes `lsp-metals-decode-file` a command which when not passed a format-id, will prompt the user for one from a preset list. I've also `defconst`ed all of the format ids so that they're not duplicated.

I hope this is helpful, thanks :slightly_smiling_face:

comment.body: Thanks.

- Built on platform(s)

  - [NixOS test(s)](https://nixos.org/manual/nixos/unstable/index.html#sec-nixos-tests) (look inside [nixos/tests](https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/blob/master/nixos/tests))

  - made sure NixOS tests are [linked](https://nixos.org/manual/nixpkgs/unstable/#ssec-nixos-tests-linking) to the relevant packages
- [ ] Tested compilation of all packages that depend on this change using `nix-shell -p nixpkgs-review --run "nixpkgs-review rev HEAD"`. Note: all changes have to be committed, also see [nixpkgs-review usage](https://github.com/Mic92/nixpkgs-review#usage)
- [x] Tested basic functionality of all binary files (usually in `./result/bin/`)
- [23.05 Release Notes (or backporting 22.11 Release notes)](https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#generating-2305-release-notes)
  - [ ] (Package updates) Added a release notes entry if the change is major or breaking
  - [ ] (Module updates) Added a release notes entry if the change is significant
  - [ ] (Module addition) Added a release notes entry if adding a new NixOS module

issue.title: Consider adding file extensions to auto-mode-alist
issue.body:
Something like:
```elisp
(add-to-list 'auto-mode-alist '("\\.mmd$" . mermaid-mode)))
```

See also https://github.com/mermaid-js/mermaid/issues/147.

I picked `mmd` because github seems to support that.

comment.body: This change broke emacs: `Invalid regexp: "Trailing backslash"`
Move `|| echo "KGlobalSettings.notifyChange failed"` after done? So that if it fails we don't get 10 messages.

pull_request.title: kconifg:init
pull_request.body:
### Description
Fixes https://github.com/nix-community/home-manager/issues/607 by providing a way to programattically set kde configuration files. 
However as note that any theme changed with this module requires a logout, as the proper way would be to exec `plasma-apply-*` and those commands seem to require a working DBus and thus https://github.com/nix-community/home-manager/pull/2548 for testing on my setup.

    ```

    ```

    See [CONTRIBUTING](https://github.com/nix-community/home-manager/blob/master/docs/contributing.adoc#sec-commit-style) for more information and [recent commit messages](https://github.com/nix-community/home-manager/commits/master) for examples.

Maybe derive this implementation: https://docs.rs/clap/latest/clap/trait.ValueEnum.html
